## 1.5ct Lab Grown vs. Natural Oval Diamond: The $6,900 Savings Case

The lab vs. natural comparison at 1.5ct is more compelling than at any other oval carat weight. Here's the math:

- Natural GIA G-VS2 1.5ct oval: **$9,835**
- IGI D-IF 1.5ct lab-grown oval: **$2,935**
- **Difference: $6,900**

For $2,935, you get a 1.5ct IGI-certified lab oval in D-IF clarity — the highest color and clarity grades available. For $9,835, you get a GIA G-VS2 natural stone of identical face-up size in a lower clarity and color tier. The lab stone has a better certificate. It looks identical or better to the naked eye. It costs $6,900 less.

The [IGI 1.5ct D-IF Ideal Cut Oval at $2,935](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/24056587?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is available in quantity on Blue Nile — 15+ stones at this exact price. The [IGI 1.5ct D-IF at $3,058](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29273375?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) represents a mild premium for specific stone proportions. The [GCAL 1.5ct D-IF at $3,128](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29417801?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) adds GCAL certification — a different lab, equally respected.

| Stone | Cert | Color/Clarity | Price | Size |
|-------|------|---------------|-------|------|
| 1.5ct Natural | GIA | G-VS2 | $9,835 | ~9.0mm × 6.5mm |
| 1.5ct Natural | GIA | E-VS2 | $8,757 | ~9.0mm × 6.5mm |
| 1.5ct Lab | IGI | D-IF | $2,935 | ~9.0mm × 6.5mm |
| 1.5ct Lab | IGI | D-IF | $3,058 | ~9.0mm × 6.5mm |
| 1.5ct Lab | GCAL | D-IF | $3,128 | ~9.0mm × 6.5mm |

The tradeoff is the same as at every carat weight: natural diamonds hold value better over time, lab diamonds depreciate aggressively. For a ring you plan to wear and never sell, the $6,900 savings is real. For a ring you might upgrade or pass down as an heirloom, natural is the defensible choice. The lab vs. natural economics are covered in full in the [lab grown diamond guide](/lab-grown-round-diamond) — the same depreciation dynamics apply to ovals.

### What About a 1.5ct Natural Oval Lab Diamond Ring Total Cost?

A 1.5ct lab oval diamond ring with a quality setting:
- [IGI D-IF at $2,935](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/24056587?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + Woven Solitaire YG ($965) = **$3,900 total**
