## 1.5ct vs. 2ct Oval Diamond: Is the Upgrade Worth It?

The 2ct oval natural GIA sweet spot starts around $22,000 — more than double the 1.5ct sweet spot price of $9,835. The [2ct oval price guide](/2-carat-oval-diamond-price) covers this in full detail, but the short answer: the 1.5ct to 2ct jump is proportionally one of the largest price increases in the oval category.

At 1.5ct, the visual is a ~9mm × 6.5mm stone. At 2ct, it becomes ~10.3mm × 7.5mm. That 1.3mm of additional length is visible but not dramatic. If you're weighing 1.5ct natural ($9,835) vs. a lab 2ct oval — that comparison is more interesting, since 2ct lab ovals can be found for similar money.

The [oval vs. round diamond comparison](/round-diamond-vs-oval-diamond) and the [princess vs. oval comparison](/princess-cut-vs-oval-diamond) both cover how oval size reads relative to other shapes at similar weights.

